webpackJsonp([0x9fbf2a041753],{1355:function(e,t){e.exports={data:{site:{siteMetadata:{title:"Psyked.co.uk",author:"James Ford"}},markdownRemark:{id:"/Users/James/Repositories/portfolio-2018/src/posts/link-working-with-sqlite-in-air-using-orm/index.md absPath of file >>> MarkdownRemark",html:'<p>If you don\'t know what ORM is read the next paragraph, and it might help.  If you do, skip to the links below to learn a little more about how you can make ORM work with AIR and SQLite.</p>\n<p>ORM stands for <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Object-relational_mapping" target="_blank">Object Relational Mapping</a>, in basic terms the concept of representing your tables-based data as more familiar objects and classes. Not a big concept after all, it\'s one that I\'ve been using already in my AIR applications - albeit unwittingly and manually.  FlexORM is a project to assist and standardise this process, so it\'s worth knowing about and trying out.</p>\n<h3>Read more about ORM:</h3>\n<a href="http://www.adobe.com/newsletters/edge/october2009/articles/article7/index.html" target="_blank">http://www.adobe.com/newsletters/edge/october2009/articles/article7/index.html</a>\n<p><a href="http://www.adobe.com/newsletters/edge/december2009/articles/article7/index.html" target="_blank">http://www.adobe.com/newsletters/edge/december2009/articles/article7/index.html</a></p>',frontmatter:{title:"Link: Working with SQLite in AIR, with the help of ORM",date:"January 28, 2010",tags:["air","flexorm","orm"]}}},pathContext:{}}}});
